  December 17-19, 2019 Kyoto, Japan
        Annual Conference on Engineering and Applied ScienceRegistration Deadline: October 13, 2019Annual Conference on Engineering and Applied Sciencewill include oral, poster sessions and feature a mix of international speakers for the Keynote Address. All the accepted research paper/ abstracts will be eligible to be presented at the conference.This year, our highlight theme will focus on "Green Technology and Environment Sustainability".Our over-consumption of the Earth's resources makes multiple crises. Recognizing that sustainable economic development is closely tied to the ability of the country to move to a low carbon climate resilient development pathway, Governments committed to find the balance between EnvironmentalProtection and Economic Development.There is no denying that Green Technologies and Environment Sustainability will be the trend and the direction to work hard.The field of Green Technologies encompasses a continuously evolving group of methods and materials, from techniques for generating energy to sustainable construction. ACEAT 2019 is designed with 9 topics consist of several subtopics that could be developed according to innovation context based on the participant's idea.TopicsEnergy Harvesting TechnologyGreen Chemical EngineeringSustainability and DesignEnvironmental EngineeringGreen ConstructionApplied ScienceLow Carbon CityEngineeringRegister NowKeynote SpeakerDr. Ramli NazirCentre of Tropical GeoengineeringUniversiti Teknologi MalaysiaTitle: Taking Risk in Geotechnical Engineering Design: Do We Learn from Failure?Local HostDr. Hiroshi UechiFaculty of CommerceOsaka Gakuin University, Japan2019 One day tour @ UjiThe conference features a wonderful socializing event: a one day tour @ Uji, the historical and culture center in ancient Japan.Contact UsWebsite: http://www.aceat.org/E-mail: aceat@aceat.org  

